      <block class="full_text">
        <p>The scandal is everywhere at the Columbia/HCA Healthcare Corporation -- in the chitchat in employee lounges, in the news articles clipped by nurses.</p>
        <p>Columbia, the $20 billion health care giant, is striving to alter its soul under the pressure of fraud investigations. It is seeking a new name, a new structure and a new purpose -- and none of it is coming easily. But it is the human dimensions that offer the most powerful illustration of the effect of the scandal.</p>
        <p>Money and Business, Section 3.</p>
      </block>
